sentences: Simon (Sim) Gokkes (21 March 1897, Amsterdam – 5 February 1943, Auschwitz) was a Dutch-Jewish composer.
Simon (Sim) Gokkes (21 March 1897, Amsterdam – 5 February 1943, Auschwitz) was a Dutch-Jewish composer.
In 1912, Gokkes wrote his first compositions, "Ngolinu Leshabiag" and "Yigdal".
He studied composition with Sem Dresden and also piano and flute at the Conservatorium van Amsterdam, finishing in 1919.
In 1921, he founded the School Choir of Amsterdam.
For years he was director of the Santo Serviçio, the choir of the Portuguese Synagogue in Amsterdam.
In 1923, Gokkes married pianist Rebecca Winnik.
Along with his wife and his two children, David and Rachel, he was murdered in Auschwitz concentration camp on 5 February 1943.
